The paper deals with analyzing the properties of a directed grid graph variation, which is a fundamental topic in computer science. The problem of collision-free traffic configuration is related to graph theory and optimization, which falls under cs.DS and cs.CG. The investigation of connectedness and shortest paths in a directed grid graph is also a common topic in robotics and artificial intelligence, which falls under cs.RO and cs.AI. Lastly, the analysis of the problem's complexity and hardness is related to computational complexity theory, which falls under cs.LG.
